name: Max Johnson
summary: UNC quarterback Max Johnson suffered a season-ending leg injury in the third quarter of North Carolina's 44-38 victory at Minnesota on Saturday. Conner Harrell replaced Johnson and led the Tar Heels to the win. The injury occurred when Johnson was sacked by Minnesota's Thomas Rush. Johnson was taken to the hospital and underwent surgery on his broken right leg. The injury is a significant blow to the Tar Heels, who are now without their starting quarterback for the remainder of the season.

name: Adnan Syed
summary: A Maryland Supreme Court has ordered a new hearing in the case of Adnan Syed, who was convicted of murder in 2000 and whose case was featured in the popular podcast "Serial." The court ruled that a lower court had erred in 2016 when it overturned Syed's conviction due to ineffective legal assistance. However, the court also upheld Syed's murder conviction, meaning that he remains behind bars. The case has garnered significant attention since it was profiled in "Serial," which explored inconsistencies in the evidence and witness testimony used to convict Syed. The new hearing is expected to focus on whether Syed received inadequate legal representation from his trial attorney, who failed to investigate alibi witnesses and request DNA testing that could have exonerated him.

name: Wheelchair basketball Paralympics
summary: In the 2024 Paralympics, the men's wheelchair basketball team made a strong start, defeating Spain in their opening match. Their victory was celebrated with a Google Doodle dedicated to wheelchair basketball. Team USA's success is particularly notable as the University of Wisconsin-Whitewater has been a key training ground for the Paralympic wheelchair basketball teams. Despite facing challenges at a TSA checkpoint, Brian Bell remains determined to achieve a three-peat in wheelchair basketball at the Paralympics. Iowans AJ Fitzpatrick and Jeromie Meyer also represent Team USA in the sport, which showcases the growing popularity and competitive spirit of wheelchair basketball at the Paralympics.

summary: Tragedy struck the NHL community as Blue Jackets star Johnny Gaudreau and his brother, Matthew, were killed in a car accident in New Jersey.
